<br>
Ok, I para-phrased that quote but you all get the idea.  I won't argue wether thats &quot;fair&quot; or not. I agree with the idea, but I think Verant was counting on the server being alittle more active population wise for this idea to work. That's why I think its an issue.<br>
<br>
Planning out your path as you level assumes the player is EXTREMELY familiar with the quests and drops available to that class. How many Dwarf/Erudite Paladins that are new to EQ will EVER discover that they need to get an item for their epic at level 9? There is NO information in Butcherblock/Kaladim/Erudin that mentions it. Is that fair?<br>
<br>
For those that say, &quot;Well, they can just look it up on the net.&quot; I would say to you, if Verant wanted folks to check spoiler sites NPC's would have hyper links on them. Or at the very least publish the URL's for these sites at eq.live.  =P<br>
<br>
Anyways, I mentioned in another post that I doubt Verant will remove the TLC on this server as it was one of the &quot;Basic concepts&quot; when they started this server. I just hope that they work on an alternate form of TLC and implement it on this server.<br>
<br>
